Class Vec2f

java.lang.Object
  cs195n.Vec2f
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public final class Vec2f
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

A class representing a two-dimensional vector of floats. Useful when working with positions and sizes in a continuous space, such as a game world. Vec2f instances, like Strings, are immutable, and should be treated in a similar way. Specifically, note that all methods will return a new instance rather than modifying the same instance, so the return value must be used or saved. For performance, this class and all of its methods have been marked final.

Author:
zdavis/dgattey

lerpTo

public final Vec2f lerpTo(Vec2f dest,
                          float frac)
Linearly interpolates between two vectors. For example, a frac value of 0 would return a vector with the same value as this vector, whereas a value of 1 would return a vector with the same value as dest and a value of .4 would return a vector four tenths of the way from this vector to dest.

Parameters:
dest - the vector to which to linearly interpolate from this vector
frac - the fraction of the distance from this vector to dest to go
Returns:
a vector that is frac amount of the distance between this vector and dest
